Ehrenfest (mean-field) dynamics have proven extremely advantageous for semiclass
ical simulations in the study of light–matter interactions.
 However, the Ehrenfest approach is sadly limited by the inability to capture
 spontaneous emission.
 To overcome this issue, a mixed quantum-classical theory for electron–radiation
 dynamics is clearly warranted.
